honed, and yet he was already half an hour late. Out of natural reverence toward the sacred crease of each trouserleg, Franz avoided sitting down and walked around the room, skirting Martha’s armchair but not daring to kiss her because of the maid’s proximity.

“I’m hungry,” said Martha. “I can’t understand why he does not come.”

“Let’s start the phonograph. You’ll teach me while we’re waiting.”

“I’m not in the mood. I said after supper.”

